In .NET MAUI Shell, you can handle all three requirements:

## 1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with `OnBackButtonPressed`

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget since the override is synchronous
            ShowUnsavedChangesDialog();
            return true; // Cancel navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowUnsavedChangesDialog()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

> **Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` only fires for the **hardware/OS back button** (Android). It does **not** fire when the user taps the Shell navbar back arrow.

## 3. Custom "Cancel" back button in the toolbar

Replace the default back arrow with a toolbar item so you control the tap:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            IsVisible="True"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>
</ContentPage>
```

Or set it inline:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                        Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

Then in your view model (or code-behind):

```csharp
[RelayCommand]
private async Task Cancel()
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");
        if (!leave) return;
    }
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
}
```

**Key points:**
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` replaces the default back-arrow action — the shell won't navigate automatically when a command is bound.
- `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the arrow with text.
- You can also use `IconOverride` if you want a custom icon instead.
- Combine both approaches to cover hardware back (Android) **and** navbar back.
